Episodes.Title: A New Hope
Episodes.Plot: The Warehouse team struggles with the horrible reality of the Warehouse's destruction and the tragic loss of Steve Jinks, Mrs. Frederic and H. G. Wells. With matters so desperate, Pete, Myka, Artie, Leena and Claudia must decide whether to knowingly use a dangerous artifact for their own personal gain ? at the risk of deadly consequences.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brent Spiner, Anthony Michael Hall, Faran Tahir, Lester Holt, Ed Schultz, CCH Pounder, Jaime Murray, Lucy Filippone, Randy Butcher, Christian Laurin, Spencer Paul, Jeffrey R. Smith

Episodes.Title: An Evil Within
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka are sent to Philadelphia to find an artifact that is the cause of strange hallucinations ? people are fearing monsters, but when attacked, only humans are killed. Artie is searching for more information on what evil he unleashed. Claudia tempts fate as she tries to bring Steve back, with the help of someone unexpected.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brent Spiner, Faran Tahir, Kate Mulgrew

Episodes.Title: Personal Effects
Episodes.Plot: A cache of Walter Skyes' stolen artifacts turn up and all six agents go into the field to recover them. Artie unexpectedly reveals his secret to Leena, while Steve begins to realize the downside of the metronome that brought him back to life.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brian J. Smith, Dee Wallace, Laura Miyata, Shailene Garnett

Episodes.Title: There's Always a Downside
Episodes.Plot: While Pete and Claudia help Hugo Miller track down a bag of marbles at a boy's academy, Myka and Steve travel to New Orleans on the trail of another artifact while Artie meets with Brother Adrian.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brent Spiner, Sam Huntington, Justin Kelly, Rene Auberjonois

Episodes.Title: No Pain, No Gain
Episodes.Plot: While Pete and Myka go to Toronto to investigate an invulnerable hockey player, Steve helps Artie track down stolen artifacts while Claudia meets with Mrs. Frederic to discuss her future as a Warehouse guardian.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mike Dopud, Kristen Nelson, Timothy Omundson, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: Fractures
Episodes.Plot: The Brotherhood continues its assault on Artie's life, targeting someone close to him with Alice Liddell, the imprisoned spirit within the Dodgson Mirror. Meanwhile, Claudia learns of the connection between herself and Steve.
Episodes.GuestStars: Lindsay Wagner, Melanie Scrofano, Niamh Wilson

Episodes.Title: Endless Wonder
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka face a curious executive from a drug company as they deal with a pill that may increase people's height. Meanwhile, Artie, Steve and Claudia follow Brother Adrian to the place where he's hiding.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brent Spiner, Faran Tahir, Danielle Nicolet, Steven Eckholdt, Jaime Murray

Episodes.Title: Second Chance
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka investigate a case of people rusting away. Steve and Claudia visit Steve's hometown to end his dependence on the Metronome. Meanwhile, Artie tells the truth about Brother Adrian and his use of the Astrolabe.
Episodes.GuestStars: Laura Innes, Pooch Hall, Jaime Murray, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: The Ones You Love
Episodes.Plot: Pete, Myka, and Claudia set off to rescue their loved ones when Brother Adrian sends them deadly artifacts. Meanwhile, Mrs. Frederic and Steve travel to Rome and learn Adrian's dark secret.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brent Spiner, Amy Acker, Jeri Ryan

Episodes.Title: We All Fall Down
Episodes.Plot: The team have no time to mourn a fallen comrade as they go after the person responsible, the nemesis that has been stalking Artie since he used Magellan's Astrolabe to save the world.
Episodes.GuestStars: Brent Spiner, CCH Pounder, Genelle Williams

Episodes.Title: The Living and the Dead
Episodes.Plot: With the fate of the world in their hands, Pete and Myka's only hope of finding a cure to the Sweating Sickness is a drunken history professor. Meanwhile, Steve and Claudia enter Artie's subconscious in an attempt to bring him out of his coma before he fades away for good.
Episodes.GuestStars: Polly Walker, James Marsters, Roger Rees, Kate Mulgrew, Thomas Roberts, Lindsay Wagner, CCH Pounder, Genelle Williams

Episodes.Title: Parks and Rehabilitation
Episodes.Plot: While Pete and Claudia travel to Oregon to investigate a series of earthquake-related accidents occurring in a National Park, Artie deals with the repercussions of Leena's death.
Episodes.GuestStars: Faran Tahir, Emily Bergl, Patrick John Flueger, Genelle Williams

Episodes.Title: The Big Snag
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka get sucked into a 1940s detective noir novel in search of an artifact. Meanwhile, Artie, Steve, and Claudia chase down a phantom car thief.
Episodes.GuestStars: Missi Pyle, Faran Tahir, America Olivo, Enrico Colantoni, Amanda Brugel

Episodes.Title: The Sky's the Limit
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka head to Vegas to investigate murders that are tied to the world of high magic. Meanwhile, Claudia and Jinks search for an artifact used to rig horse races, while Artie meets the new B&B owner, Abigail Cho.
Episodes.GuestStars: Polly Walker, Joel Grey, Kelly Hu, Nora Zehetner, Steve Valentine, CCH Pounder, Goldy Notay, Tara Joshi

Episodes.Title: Instinct
Episodes.Plot: H.G. has created a new life for herself in Wisconsin, but calls in the agents when she comes up against an unidentified artifact. Meanwhile, Abigail joins the others on the floor of the Warehouse to track down the source of mysterious tremors that threaten to destroy the building.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kelly Hu, Todd Stashwick, Tuc Watkins, Ricardo Chavira, Jaime Murray, Eric Murdoch, Imali Perera

Episodes.Title: Runaway
Episodes.Plot: When a volcanic event at an Arkansas State Prison allows two inmates to escape, Pete, Myka and Steve must partner with a U.S. Marshal to track down the fugitives.
Episodes.GuestStars: Charlie Weber, Cherie Currie, Vladimir Jon Cubrt, Ronnie Rowe, Mary Krohnert

Episodes.Title: What Matters Most
Episodes.Plot: Someone in a gated community is using an artifact to extract vengeance and Myka and Pete go to investigate. Meanwhile, Artie and Claudia help a teen suffering from dangerous visions, and Steve and Abigail clean up the Warehouse.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kelly Hu, Chris Ellis, Cynthia Watros, Josh Blaylock

Episodes.Title: Lost and Found
Episodes.Plot: The agents track down a cache of artifacts stolen from Warehouse 12 by the infamous Roaring Dan Seavey... and guarded by his ghost. Meanwhile, Charlotte Dupres makes her move with the help of her inside person.
Episodes.GuestStars: Polly Walker, Anthony Head, Sasha Roiz, Josh Blaylock, Reed Clare

Episodes.Title: All the Time in the World
Episodes.Plot: Pete, Myka, and Charlotte must track down Sutton, the only man who knows where they can find Paracelsus and exchange the Philosopher's Stone for the stele that will free Claudia from her bronze imprisonment... before she disintegrates.
Episodes.GuestStars: Polly Walker, Anthony Head, James Marsters, Kelly Hu, Faran Tahir, Josh Blaylock, CCH Pounder

Episodes.Title: The Truth Hurts
Episodes.Plot: Pete and Myka capture Paracelsus but not before he makes himself immortal. When Myka's cancer becomes worse, Pete must make a deal with Paracelsus to cure his partner. Meanwhile, Claudia receives some startling news from Artie.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsters, Anthony Head, Kelly Hu, Josh Blaylock, CCH Pounder, Genelle Williams
